{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Dough","content":["Place yeast, eggs, sugar and milk in mixing bowl then heat <b>3 min\/37°C\/speed 2<b>.","Add remaining dough ingredients and knead <b>4 min\/<b>. Transfer to a large bowl, cover with cling film and leave to prove in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 2½ hours). Clean mixing bowl.","Preheat oven to 170°C and line 2 baking trays with baking paper.","Place dough on a lightly-floured work surface. Roll out into a rectangle (approx. 30 cm x 45 cm x 5 mm) and cut into 16 rectangles."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Place blueberries, sugar and flour in mixing bowl then mix <b>2 sec\/\/speed 2<b>.","Spoon an equal amount of mixture into the middle of each rectangle of dough then, working with one piece at a time, pinch all four corners together into the middle to encase the filling. Seal well, then lightly roll between your hands to shape into ovals. Place buns seam-side down onto prepared baking trays and allow to prove for 15 minutes.","Brush egg over each bun and bake for 25 minutes (170°C) until lightly golden. Transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.","Top with royal icing (if using) and serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Dough","content":["2 tsp dried instant yeast","2 medium eggs","110 g sugar","100 g whole milk","370 g strong white bread flour","50 g unsalted butter, soft","1 tsp vanilla extract","1 pinch fine sea salt"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["250 g fresh blueberries","70 g sugar","30 g plain flour","1 medium egg, lightly beaten, for brushing","royal icing              (optional)"]}],"id":"r105448","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-rUXqnj_vRpY\/XZavF6geDGI\/AAAAAAAAhrM\/ZzKh3DxbJbQDHehyyYvu1MFnEcCoRc4ZwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_deIeQIGd4kuAEeM-.png","title":"Blueberry Breakfast Buns","publishedAt":"2017-12-25T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.6 g","fat":"5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"46.8 g","calories":"1041 kJ \/ 248 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, 